\n< Priest >The doors of God's house are always open to
everyone. If you feel weary in your heart, please
come and find solace anytime.
\n< Old Man >.......

\n< Serena >Not even a flinch.... He seems to be praying very
fervently.
\n< Old Man >......zzz.
\n< Serena >.......

\n< Devout Woman >O great Lord, please bless my husband and me with
a child...

\n< Devout man >Children are a gift from the Lord, the fruit of
the womb is a reward... O Lord, please...

\n< Devout man >The Lord sees through our hearts. That's why I
travel to various churches and offer prayers
wholeheartedly.
\n< Old woman >.......

\n< Serena >Not even a twitch... You must be praying very
fervently.
\n< Serena >It's a pipe organ.
\n< Serena >The church organ is generally out of tune.

\n< Serena >I have had the opportunity to play it in several
churches, and without exception, they made me stop
playing it.

\n< Serena >Probably the same here. I can tell just by looking
at it.
\n< Serena >There's a book.

\n< Serena >As part of our spiritual training, we copy
manuscripts at the church. Thanks to this
practice, a lot of wisdom has been passed down to
this day.

\n< Serena >Well, it seems that the books lined up here are
all simple ones for the believers.
\n< Serena >Here's the book.
